      <h2>Why Traditional SEO Is Not Enough</h2>
      <p>Traditional SEO optimizes for ranking factors in Google's algorithm: backlinks, keyword density, page speed, mobile usability. These still matter. But AI search engines use different signals to decide what to cite. They do not have a "SERP" in the traditional sense — they generate answers by synthesizing information from multiple sources.</p>
      <p>When ChatGPT answers a question, it decides which sources to reference based on: how well the content answers the specific question, whether the source is authoritative on the topic, how recently the content was published, and whether the source has clear authorship and trust signals. A page that ranks #8 on Google might be cited by ChatGPT while the #1 result is ignored, if the #8 page has better structured data and clearer expertise signals.</p>
      <p>The AI Visibility Checker bridges this gap. It evaluates the signals that specifically matter for AI citation, separate from traditional ranking factors. Use it alongside your existing SEO tools for a complete picture of your search presence.</p>

